The '''Institute for Advanced Study, [[Tsinghua University]]''' ('''CASTU'''; {{zh|s=清华大学高等研究院|p=Qīnghuá Dàxué Gāodĕng Yánjiū Yuàn}}) is a research institute established in [[Beijing]] in 1997. Modelled after the Princeton-based [[Institute for Advanced Study]], albeit in a university setting, it is engaged in theoretical studies in [[Theoretical physics|physics]], [[Theoretical computer science|computer science]] and [[Theoretical biology|biology]]. Its honorary director is the [[Nobel Laureate]] professor [[Chen Ning Yang]], who has provided guidance and support to CASTU since its inception, and current director is professor [[Gu Binglin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.castu.tsinghua.edu.cn/publish/cas/1696/2012/20120406111427772597752/20120406111427772597752_.html|title=顾秉林——教授，院长|last=|first=|date=|website=|language=Chinese|trans-title=Gu Binglin - Professor, Director|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-02-21}}</ref>
