{{multiple issues| {{no footnotes|date=July 2012}} {{one source|date=July 2012}} }}
{{Infobox book | name = Queers In History | image = QueersInHistory.GIF | caption = 2009 edition cover | author = [[Keith Stern]] | publisher = [[Benbella Books]] | pages = 587 (U.S. trade paperback) | isbn = 1-933771-87-9 | oclc= 317453194 }} '''''Queers in History''''' is an [[encyclopedia]] written by [[Keith Stern]] of historically prominent people who were [[lesbian]], [[gay]], [[bisexual]], or [[transgender]] ([[LGBT]]).
It was first published on [[diskette]] in early 1993, and in an expanded [[CD-ROM]] format by the end of 1994. It was one of the first [[new media]] titles to be distributed through bookstores. It was available in over 600 [[independent bookstores]] worldwide, and at selected locations of leading book selling chains in the UK and US. It went out of print in 1996.
A new, completely revised edition was published as a [[Paperback#Trade paperback|trade paperback]] by [[BenBella Books]] in September 2009. It features a foreword by [[Ian McKellen]].
